    "en": {
      "title": "Deployment of Dornier 220 Aircraft gifted by India to SLAF",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mutual security, safety of India and Sri Lanka is not only beneficial to both nations but to the entire region, Indian High Commissioner Gopal Baglay said today.",
        "Speaking during the deployment of Dornier 220 Aircraft gifted by India to the Sri Lanka Air Force, Mr. Baglay said the gifting of the new aircraft will serve this purpose.",
        "\"The new Dornier Aircraft is an example of India' s value of ensuring that benefits of a strong India is shared in the region,\" he said.",
        "\"India is celebrating 75th anniversary of its independence. Story of India's independence came along with struggles. With these struggles, India had become a strong entity that had uplifted the literacy and uplifted its people from poverty. India is in the world map today as a nation with the largest manpower team. India has also maintained its values and tradition of helping all mankind,\" he added.",
        "He noted that India's foreign policy of neighbours first and Sagara is also directed towards helping the region. (Yohan Perera)"
      ],
